'''Acharya Institute of Technology''' ('''AIT''', {{lang-kn|<U+0C86><U+0C9A><U+0CBE><U+0CB0><U+0CCD><U+0CAF><U+0CBE> <U+0C87><U+0CA8><U+0CCD><U+0CB8><U+0CCD><U+0C9F><U+0CBF><U+0C9F><U+0CCD><U+0CAF><U+0CC2><U+0C9F><U+0CCD> <U+0C86><U+0CAB><U+0CCD> <U+0C9F><U+0CC6><U+0C95><U+0CCD><U+0CA8><U+0CBE><U+0CB2><U+0C9C><U+0CBF>}}) is a private [[Mixed-sex education|co-educational]] engineering and management college in [[Bangalore]], [[India]]. AIT is affiliated with the [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]] and is [[accredited]] by the [[National Board of Accreditation]]. Established in 2000, it offers eleven courses at undergraduate level and six courses at postgraduate level.<ref name="bare_url">{{cite web|author=(c) 2009 Acharya Institutes |url=http://acharya.ac.in/ait.html |title=Top Engineering College in Bangalore, 10 best engineering college in bangalore as per CSR rankings |publisher=Acharya.ac.in |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>
AIT includes the NRV School of Architecture, which offers a five-year undergraduate course in [[architecture]] and is accredited by the [[Council of Architecture]] (COA).<ref name="coa">{{cite web|url=http://www.coa.gov.in/STATUS.pdf |title=CoA |publisher=Govt of India |date= |accessdate=2011-11-30}}</ref><ref name="bare_url_h">{{cite web|author=(c) 2009 Acharya Institutes |url=http://acharya.ac.in/asa.html |title=School of architecture, B Arch at Bangalore, Acharya NRV School of Architecture |publisher=ASA |date=2010-10-04 |accessdate=2011-11-30}}</ref> The college has various collaborations and tie-ups with various industries and universities across the world.<ref>{{cite web|author=(c) 2009 Acharya Institutes |url=http://acharya.ac.in/studentlife.html |title=Acharya Institutes, Soldevanahalli Bangalore |publisher=Acharya Institutes |date= |accessdate=2011-11-30}}</ref>

It is one of the several institutes run by the JMJ Education Society<ref name="bare_url_j" /> and features in various rankings lists of top engineering colleges in India published by media agencies and publications like ''[[Outlook (magazine)|Outlook]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pescemandya.org/images/outlook_pse.jpg |title=PESCE ranking archives |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> [[Competition Success Review|CSR-GHRDC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharya.ac.in/csr.php Top Engineering college of Bangalore. Best engineering college at bangalore ranked 10th best by CSR survey|title=Top Engineering college of Bangalore|publisher=CSR |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref> ''[[Dataquest]]'',<ref name="bare_url_e">{{cite web|author=Cyber India Online Ltd. |url=http://dqindia.ciol.com/content/top_stories/2005/105052301.asp |title=Dataquest : Top Stories : The Complete Scorecard |publisher=Dqindia.ciol.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref><ref name="bare_url_f">{{cite web|author=Cyber India Online Ltd. |url=http://dqindia.ciol.com/content/top_stories/2007/107062204.asp |title=Dataquest : Top Stories : The Complete Scorecard 2007 |publisher=Dqindia.ciol.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref><ref name="cybermedia">{{cite web|url=http://www.cybermedia.co.in/press/pressrelease46.html Cyber Media|title=DQ Rankings|publisher=Dataquest|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> ''[[NASSCOM|NASSCOM and Silicon India]]'',<ref name="scribd">{{cite web|url=http://www.scribd.com/doc/46148119/Top-100-Eng-Colleges Top 100 Eng Colleges|title=NASSCOM and SI Rankings|publisher=NASSCOM|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> ''[[Electronics For You|EFY]]''.<ref name="iudehradun">{{cite web|url=http://www.iudehradun.edu.in/Top50-engineering-supplement_May11.pdf |title=EFY |publisher=DQ |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref> In 2011 rankings, AIT was ranked among the top five Engineering colleges in [[Karnataka]] by the Global Human Resources Development Centre (GHRDC).<ref name="bare_url_d">{{cite web|url=http://ghrdc.org/pdfs/statewise_results11.pdf |title=GHRDC statewise ranking list |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>
It features as an ''A+ institution'' in the rankings of the publication ''[[Outlook (magazine)|Career 360]]''.<ref name="careers360">{{cite web|url=http://www.careers360.com/news/4339-India-s-Best-Engineering-Colleges-Other-Ranking-of-E-Schools |title=Think higher education! Engineering schools: We analyse previous rankings! |publisher=Careers360 |date=2010-06-03 |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> The college was also conferred with ''South India's Excellent Institution Award'' by A-Plus TV Media Works.<ref name="bare_url_i">{{cite web|author=(c) 2009 Acharya Institutes |url=http://acharya.ac.in/ |title=Engineering College Bangalore, MBA PGDM Management College Bangalore, Pharmacy, nursing, fashion, journalism courses at Bangalore, India |publisher=Acharya.ac.in |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref>

AIT organises an annual week-long inter-collegiate [[culfest|cultural fest]] known as the ''Acharya Habba'', which is one of the largest in Bangalore and Karnataka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://expressbuzz.com/cities/bangalore/a-fiery-performance-at-acharya-habba/264926.html A fiery performance at Acharya Habba %7C Acharya Habba %7C %7C The New Indian Express|title=A fiery performance at Acharya Habba |publisher=The New Indian Express |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knowafest.com/2011/03/acharya-habba-2011-acharya-institutes.html Acharya Habba 2011, Acharya Institutes, Technical cum Cultural Festival, Bangalore, Karnataka, April 7<U+2013>9, 2011 : Acharya Habba 11, April 2011, Bangalore, Cultural Fest, Cultura...|title=Technical cum Cultural Festival|publisher=knowafest|date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/04/06/stories/2011040652040200.htm The Hindu : Karnataka / Bangalore News : Three-day Acharya Habba starts tomorrow|title=Three-day Acharya Habba starts tomorrow|publisher=The Hindu|date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref>

The postgraduate courses in the institute, especially [[MBA]], makes it one of most notable colleges in the Karnataka Management Aptitude Test (KMAT).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/178652/a-welcome-option-mba-aspirants.html |title=A welcome option for MBA aspirants |publisher=Deccanherald.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>
