== History ==
The Acharya Institute of Technology (AIT) was established in 2000 by Shri Premnath Reddy, chairman of Acharya Group of Institutions.<ref name="bare_url_k" /> The college is managed by the JMJ Education Society, headquartered in Bangalore.<ref name="bare_url_j" />
AIT offers the [[Bachelor of Engineering]] course in eleven disciplines, and [[Master of Technology]] in four disciplines: [[Data transmission|Digital Communication Engineering]] and [[Biotechnology]], [[Computer Science and Engineering]], [[Machine|Machine Design]], [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] and [[Master of Computer Applications|MCA]]. All courses are affiliated to the Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU).<ref name="bare_url" />

[[File:Acharya Institute of Technology Campus.jpg||200px|thumb|The Acharyan emblem with motto and mission]]

It was the first college under the VTU to start an undergraduate course in [[Mechatronics|Mechatronics Engineering]] in Karnataka.<ref name="bare_url_b">{{cite web|url=http://vtu.ac.in/index.php/affiliated-institutes/114.html?article= Acharya Institute Of Technology|title=Affiliated-institutes|publisher=VTU|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref name="deccanherald_a">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/120857/students-principles-thats-acharyas-aim.html Students with principles, that<U+2019>s Acharya<U+2019>s aim|title=Students with principles, that's Acharya's aim|publisher=The Deccan Herald|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

In 2009, the college constructed a {{Convert|3|km|mi|adj=on}} long road from its campus to the Hessarghatta Main Road. The road was inaugurated by [[Sree Sree Shivakumara Swamiji]] of Siddaganga Math in September 2010. The road is named after former [[President of India|Indian President]] [[Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan]] and is known as ''Acharya Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan Road''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/online_magazine/event_details.php?dt=2010-10-05 Event Details|title=''Acharya Dr. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan Road'' inaugurated|publisher=Acharya Samachar|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/canvasartrajaram/docs/ai_ebrochure_2011 Acharya Institutes eBrochure|title=Road inaugurated|publisher=AI|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

== Academic profile ==
===Admission criteria===
[[File:Achrya1.jpg|250px|right|thumb|Acharya Institute of Technology Campus]]
AIT admits students on basis of their [[Common Entrance Test|Karnataka CET]] or their COMEDK UGET ranks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comedk.org/uget/MemberInstitute.aspx COMEDK <U+2013> Consortium of Medical, Engineering and Dental Colleges of Karnataka|title=Member Institutes|publisher=COMEDK UGET|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> AIT also admits students under Management quota, which does not place any merit requirements.

Yearly, AIT admits over 150 foreign nationals from 25 countries under the [[Non-resident Indian and Person of Indian Origin|PIO Quota]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/nice2010/broucher.pdf |title=NICE brochure |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/nacc2011/Home.html Untitled Document|title=NACC 2011|publisher=AI|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

There is a lateral entry scheme in place, by which students holding diploma degrees can enter directly to the second year of study In engineering. Students, after completing their graduation, receive a [[Bachelor of Engineering|B.E.]] degree from the VTU.

Students are admitted to postgraduate courses on basis of their [[Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering|GATE]] test scores, as well as on their [[Common Entrance Test|Karnataka Post Graduate CET]] (PGCET) and KMAT PGCET scores.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kmatindia.com/ParticipatingColleges.htm KMAT 2011|title=Participating colleges|publisher=KMAT|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

