;Undergraduate courses
The college offers four year [[Bachelor of Engineering]] courses in 11 disciplines. All of these following courses are affiliated with the Visvesvaraya Technological University.<ref name="bare_url" /><ref name="bare_url_a">{{cite web|url=http://vtu.ac.in/index.php/affiliated-institutes/114.html?article= |title=Acharya Institute Of Technology |publisher=Vtu.ac.in |date=2009-08-11 |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>
* [[Aeronautical Engineering]]
* [[Automobile Engineering]]
* [[Biotechnology]]
* [[Civil Engineering]]
* [[Computer Science]]
* [[Construction|Construction technology]]
* [[Electronics engineering|Electronics & Communication Engineering]]
* [[Electrical engineering|Electrical & Electronics Engineering]]
* [[Mechatronics Engineering]]
* [[Mechanical Engineering]]
* [[Information science|Information Science & Engineering]]

;Post Graduate courses
In addition to the [[Bachelor of Engineering|B.E.]] courses, the college offers two year [[Master of Technology]] courses in four disciplines, [[MBA]] and [[Master of Computer Applications|MCA]]. All of the following courses are affiliated with the Visvesvaraya Technological University.<ref name="bare_url" />
* [[Master of Business Administration]] (MBA)
* [[Master of Computer Applications]] (MCA)
* [[Master of Technology]] in [[Biotechnology]]
* [[Master of Technology]] in [[Computer Science and Engineering]]
* [[Master of Technology]] in [[Digital Electronics|Digital Communication Engineering]]
* [[Master of Technology]] in [[Machine|Machine Design]]

;Architecture
Acharya's NRV School of Architecture (ASA) offers a five year undergraduate course in [[architecture]] ([[B.Arch]]), which is accredited by the [[Council of Architecture]] (COA).<ref name="coa" /><ref name="bare_url_h" />

===Faculty===
AIT maintains a Teacher-student ratio of 1:10.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Faculty-Student ratio|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/120857/students-principles-thats-acharyas-aim.html|accessdate=2012-01-15|publisher=DH}}</ref>

It is the first college in Karnataka to put in effect the [[Sixth Central Pay Commission]] recommendations for faculty pay scale.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seasonalmagazine.com/2011/07/acharya-can-move-up-by-attracting.html Seasonal Magazine: Acharya Can Move Up By Attracting Talent and Updating Infrastructure|title=Acharya Can Move Up By Attracting Talent and Updating Infrastructure |publisher=Seasonal Magazine |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

===Research Centers===

The Visvesvaraya Technological University has recognised four departments of AIT as [[Research|Research Centers]].<ref name="bare_url" /><ref name="bare_url_a" />

The Institute receives MODROBS grant from [[AICTE]] for research activities and upgraded state of art lab facilities.<ref name="bare_url" />

The following departments of the college are recognised as [[Research|Research Centers]]:
<ref name="bare_url_a" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://vtu.ac.in/pdf/Circulars/list2011.pdf |title=VTU circulars |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

* Department of [[Bio-technology]]

* Department of [[Electronics and Communication Engineering]]

* Department of [[Mathematics]]

* Department of [[Mechanical Engineering]]

