AIT is one of the few colleges in Karnataka to be [[accredited]] by the [[National Board of Accreditation]] (NBA).<ref>{{cite web|author=(c) 2009 Acharya Institutes |url=http://acharya.ac.in/ait.html |title=Top Engineering College in Bangalore, 10 best engineering college in bangalore as per CSR rankings |publisher=AIT |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref> It was the first college under the Visvesvaraya Technological University to start an undergraduate course in [[Mechatronics|Mechatronics Engineering]] in [[Karnataka]].<ref name="bare_url_b" />
It is one of the seven colleges in Karnataka to be funded by the [[World Bank]] and is granted endowments by the Visvesvaraya Technological University to carry out research works in both its undergraduate and postgraduate departments.<ref name="deccanherald_a" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://info.worldbank.org/etools/docs/library/252229/Acharya%20Institute%20of%20Technology,%20Bangalore.pdf |title=World Bank |publisher=World bank |date= |accessdate=2011-11-28}}</ref>

The college is ranked consistently among the top 50 Engineering colleges in India by publications and organizations namely [[Outlook India]],<ref name="outlookindia">{{cite web|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?265887 www.outlookindia.com %7C Top 50 Engineering Colleges|title=Top 50 engineering colleges in India |publisher=Outlook India |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref name="nitk">{{cite web|url=http://www.nitk.ac.in/assets/files/aieee/outlook.pdf |title=NITK assests archive |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>  [[Dataquest|Data Quest]],<ref name="bare_url_e" /><ref name="bare_url_f" /><ref name="cybermedia" />  [[NASSCOM|NASSCOM and Silicon India]],<ref name="scribd" /> [[Electronics For You|EFY]],<ref name="iudehradun" /> [[Competition Success Review|CSR-GHRDC]]<ref name="bare_url_c">{{cite web|url=http://ghrdc.org/pdfs/overall_results11.pdf |title=GHRDC ranking 2011 |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref name="bare_url_c" /> and [[Competition Success Review|CSR]].<ref name="acharya">{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/csr.php Top Engineering college of Bangalore. Best engineering college at bangalore ranked 10th best by CSR survey|title=Best engineering college at bangalore |publisher=CSR |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>  AIT was ranked among the top 5 Engineering colleges in Karnataka by the Global Human Resources Development Centre(GHRDC).<ref name="bare_url_d" /> It was also bestowed ''South India's Excellent Institution Award''
by A-Plus TV Media Works.<ref name="bare_url_i" />

AIT features as an ''A+ institution'' in the rankings of the publication [[Outlook (magazine)|Career 360]].<ref name="careers360" />

==Administration==

===Governing council===
The governing council of the college consists of 11 members. The body comprises five members from the JMJ Education Society, one staff representative, one&nbsp;[[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Commission]] member, one [[AICTE]] nominee, one [[Government of Karnataka|state government]], Dept. of Technical Education nominee, one university nominee, and one Member Secretary, the principal.<ref name="acharya_a" /><ref name="bare_url_g">{{cite web|url=http://info.worldbank.org/etools/docs/library/252229/Acharya%20Institute%20of%20Technology,%20Bangalore.pdf |title=World bank |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-11-29}}</ref>

===Academic council===
The academic council of the college is headed by the principal. Student enrollments, academics, assessments, examinations are managed by the respective deans, controller of examinations and appointed faculty members. The college administration is managed by the director of administration. The research department is headed by the director of R&D. The placement department is managed by the principal, director of HR and one expert in the subject. Each academic department is headed by respective heads of departments (HoDs).<ref name="acharya_a" /><ref name="bare_url_g" />

===Proctorial system===
Faculty members are appointed as proctors for the students of their respective departments to monitor their attendance, performance in tests, co-curricular activities and personality development. Each proctor supervises 20 students in an academic semester.<ref name="acharya_a" /><ref name="bare_url_g" />

== Campus ==
[[File:Multi-function Stadium, Acharya Institute of Technology.jpg|thumb|right|190px|AIT Stadium]]

;'''Educational facilities'''

The college has a ''Central Library'' with  ''[[EDUSAT (Satellite)|EDUSAT]] programmes'', ''[[E-learning]] facilities'' and  ''[[Online Public Access Catalog]]'' (OPAC) gateway.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/canvasartrajaram/docs/acharya_ebrochure Acharya Institutes eBrochure|title=Library facilities |publisher=issuu.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

The institution has various has collaborations with [[Multinational Corporation]]s and has established various learning facilities like ''Vasundhara Industrial [[Automation]] Learning Center'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vasundara.com/products/pdf/IALC_Brochure.pdf |title=IALC brochure |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> ''[[IBM]] Software Center of Excellence'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www-07.ibm.com/in/university/coe.html IBM Software Centre of Excellence <U+2013> India|title=IBM Software Centre of Excellence   |publisher=IBM |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> ''[[Microsoft]] IT Academy'',<ref name="bare_url" /> and  ''[[Novell]] Centre of Excellence''.<ref name=autogenerated4 />

''International Academy for Competency Enhancement'' (IACE), the [[Finishing School]] of Acharya Institutes provides soft skills and technical trainings to students.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forayanimation.com/about_iace.html Animation Academy %7CAnimation Training India%7C Animation School %7C Animation colleges %7C Animations Degree %7CBFA in Animation %7C Animation Classes %7C Animation Centre India %7C 2d 3d A...|title=International Academy for Competency Enhancement  |publisher=IACE |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

;'''Entrepreneur Incubation Cell'''

The college and signed an [[Memorandum of Understanding]] (MoU) with IBM and has established ''IBM Entrepreneur Incubation Center'' in the campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/online_magazine/event_details.php?dt=2010-10-25 Event Details|title=Entrepreneur Center Inaugaration   |publisher=Acharya Samachar |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www-07.ibm.com/in/university/coepics.html IBM Software Centre of Excellence Pictures <U+2013> India|title=Entrepreneur Incubation Center   |publisher=IBM |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

;'''Infrastructure'''

The college provides a  24/7 campus ''[[Wi-Fi]] access''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arubanetworks.com/news-releases/acharya-institutes-consolidates-campus-wide-wi-fi-access-using-aruba-networks-802-11n-solution/ Acharya Institutes Consolidates Campus-Wide Wi-Fi Access Using Aruba Networks<U+2019> 802.11n Solution %7C Aruba Networks|title=Campus-Wide Wi-Fi Access Using Aruba Networks |publisher=Aruba Networks |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> The college has an Auditorium with a capacity of 500+ seats,  Board rooms,  Conference and Seminar Halls. The institution has its own multipurpose stadium known as the ''Smt. Nagarathnama Stadium'' with a capacity of over 10,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/03/26/stories/2011032657192000.htm The Hindu : Sport / Cricket : Somashekar shines|title=Sport / Cricket |publisher=The Hindu|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> The college also has a ''National Technical Manpower Information System'' (NTMIS)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nitk.ac.in/index.php?q=mca1.html NITKSurathkal_MCA|title=NTMIS|publisher=NITK|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref> and 24/7 ''ATM center/outlet'' operated by [[Axis Bank]]. The college operates a Campus clinic which provides medical facilities to the students.

;'''Environmental Initiatives'''

The institution has built its own sewage treatment plant in the campus and has employed methods for rain water harvesting. The campus also boasts of a four-acre artificial lake.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/Sustainable_Built_Environments_Workshop.pdf |title=SBEW |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

;'''Hostels and Canteens'''

AIT provides Hostel Accommodation for both boys and girls. The Hostel Mess serves North Indian, South Indian and Chinese cuisine.
The college has separate Food Court, Cafeteria and Canteen which serve vegetarian food in the campus. The campus also houses a ''Coffee Day Xpress'' operated by the [[Coffee Day]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coffeedayxpress.com/about-us.html About Us|title=Coffee day express in Campus  |publisher=Coffee day express |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

;'''Recreational Facilities'''

The college has a ''Student activity center'' which provides indoor games and gymnasium facilities. The institution also organises horse riding and yoga learning camps on campus for the students.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/campus%20movie.php Capmus Movie with excellent facilities for students at Acharya Institutes, Soldevanahalli Bangalore, India|title=Facilities for students |publisher=AI |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/ebrochure.php | title=Brochure | publisher=AIT | accessdate=December 17, 2011}}</ref>

== Industry interaction ==
[[File:IBM center of excellence, Acharya Institute of Technology.jpg|thumb|right|150px|IBM Entrepreneur Incubation Center]]

The college has industry collaborations and has signed [[Memorandum of Understanding]] (MoUs) with [[Computer Society of India]] (CSI), Environ Software Pvt Ltd, IBM, [[Infosys]], [[Indian Society for Technical Education|ISTE]], [[Keane (company)|Keane]], [[Microsoft]], [[Novell]], [[Oracle]], [[SAP Labs]], [[Sun Microsystems]], [[United Technologies]], Vasundhara Automation and Engineering Services Pvt. Ltd. (VAES), [[VMware]], [[Wipro]]  and many other leading companies to increase the industry interaction.<ref name=autogenerated4 /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www-07.ibm.com/in/academicinitiative/testimonial/ IBM <U+2013> Testimonials <U+2013> India|title=Academic initiative |publisher=IBM |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efytimes.com/e1/50893/fullnews.htm Novell Announces New SUSE Linux Certification Programmes|title=Novell Announces New SUSE Linux Certification Programmes |publisher=EFY Times |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.environsoftware.com/clients.aspx Environ Software (P) Ltd|title=Environ Software clients |publisher=Environ Software(P) Ltd |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

== University twinning programs ==
AIT has [[International education|twinning programs]] with foreign universities for student exchange programme and higher studies. Some of them are [[Jiujiang University]], [[Shandong University]], [[Ocean University of China]] and [[Hefei University]] in [[China]]; [[Old Dominion University]] in [[USA]]; [[Thames Valley University]] in [[UK]]; [[Andalusia Technology Park]] in [[Spain]]; [[Fachhochschule L<U+00FC>beck|L<U+00FC>beck University of Applied Sciences]] in [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/online_magazine/event_details.php?dt=2011-5-16 Event Details|title=University Tie-ups |publisher=Acharya Samachar |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

The college also has tie-ups with [[Mysore University]], [[Mysore]] and [[Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay]] (IIT-B) in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acharya.ac.in/online_magazine/event_details.php?dt=2011-10-17|title=IIT-Bombay Tie-up |publisher=Acharya Samachar |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

== Cultural activities ==
[[File:Benny dayal@acharya habba.jpg|thumb|right|200px| Singer [[Benny Dayal]] performing in Acharya Habba 2011]]

;'''Acharya Habba'''

The college organises an annual inter-collegiate [[culfest]] known as the "Acharya Habba" which sees a crowd of over 30000 students from over 300 colleges across Karnataka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youthv.com/content/view/844/58/ YOUTHV THE VOICE OF YOUTH IN DELHI AND AROUND <U+2013> Acharya Habba 2011 @ Bangalore|title=VOICE OF YOUTH |publisher=Youth V|date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edusutra.com/acharya-habba-2011-acharya-institutes-bangalore/532 Acharya HABBA 2011- Acharya Institutes, Bangalore EduSutra.com %7C EduSutra.com|title=Habba-2011 |publisher=Edusutra.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://5528319603800456285-a-1802744773732722657-s-sites.googlegroups.com/site/aigslibrary/config/pagetemplates/newspaper-clippings/achaya-habba.pdf?attachauth=ANoY7cqRtQDdGk0McUbL1s3lDHPxYM7xsF5P8JzkLYHBRFjMb-IW5dI2bcIwiotfF9d8s4Xps2qwi3dF_mprFMWSYeTEPNjEIT70qsPBaZ7FgnMtVFda8za7UgBWdT1LwRxnBO3Ne7ux9IWMvZDAUjAVellgREs3uTDq6sZiZIS1OGszDN48X-hLGZf1bpiMxkrFB6iJZ7iu-xcOQX0_esGrYBHEESWJRA9hgB8MXApDKRakkmA2c1qPLUmXU06RIxgIKnEdjCof&attredirects=0 |title=Download Attachment |publisher=Edusutra.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

;'''Ethnic day'''

Students dress up in their traditional clothes highlighting the cultural importance of the region they belong to.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharyainstitutesblog.blogspot.com/2011/03/ethnic-day-by-royal-mech-acharya2011.html Acharya Institutes: Ethnic day by Royal Mech Acharya 2011|title=Ethnic day |publisher=Royal Mech, AIT |date=2011-09-28 |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

;'''Freshers' day'''

The [[Fresher]]s are welcomed by the seniors of various departments of the college in an extravagant and cheerful way. The students of the college organise various cultural, extra-curricular and technical activities to greet and encourage the freshers who have joined the college.
Various stalls are organised by different departments and clubs of the college to exhibit the facilities, rules & regulations and achievements of the college.<ref name="deccanherald">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/194297/glimpse-college-life.html |title=Glimpse of college life |publisher=Deccanherald.com |date=2011-09-28 |accessdate=2011-10-29}}</ref>

